Helpful tips for parents from Ms. Baker:

1. No one is perfect. In this strange time take this opportunity to spend time with the people you love. Your children will thank you for those special moments and remember these times forever.
2.Take your own breaks, try yoga or mindfulness and then teach these things to your children.
3. Get moving. Having dance parties and showing your kids some of your moves...priceless.
4.Remember to be flexible. Nothing stays the same these days.

Remember...We are in this together

Need extra help:
Mon-Fri. 8am-3pm
ibaker@msdaz.org
480-334-3617

United Food Bank
March 24 at 5:40 PM ¬∑

**IMPORTANT UPDATE**

United Food Bank's Help Yourself program is moving to the Mesa Convention Center for a drive-thru style food distribution this Friday from 8 a.m. to noon.

WHAT: Help Yourself Food Distribution

WHEN: Friday, March 27 from 8 a.m. to noon

WHERE: Mesa Convention Center, 263 N. Center St., Mesa, AZ

DRIVERS: You must empty out your trunks prior to arriving so we can safely and quickly load your food. Enter from University Drive onto N. Centennial Way. Please see green lines on the map and pay attention to the volunteers directing traffic.

WALK-INS: If you are arriving by foot or bike, go to the walk-in area indicated in light blue on the map.

REMINDER: If you are feeling any cold or flu symptoms, especially cough, fever or shortness of breath, please stay home and seek treatment so you can get better.

Thank you and please let us know if you have any questions!

30th Ave & Pima St. NE corner
36th Drive & Tonto St. NW corner
21st Ave & Sherman St. NE corner

On Tuesday, March 17, we began a curbside meal service for our students & community. We are offering free breakfast and lunch to all children 18 years old and younger. Jack L. Kuban Elementary School
3201 West Sherman St. 85009

We will continue to communicate with families via our website (www.msdaz.org) and social media accounts.

post_text:
The following information has been provided by the Auditor General's Office.

Our peer group are districts similar in size and demographics to Murphy.

In 2017 Murphy School District spent 45.4% of all dollars on Instruction, our peer group average was 51.3%.
In 2018 Murphy School District spent 48.4% of all dollars on Instruction, our peer group average was 51.4%.
In 2019 Murphy School District spent 53.3% of all dollars on Instruction, our peer group average is 52.2%.
In 2018 we spent $5,241 on Instruction per student.
In 2019 we spent $5,443 on Instruction per student...2019 the State average was $4,869 and 2019 our peer group was $4,648"

https://www.azauditor.gov/sites/default/files/20-201_Report_with_Pages.pdf

Community Notification:

Murphy Elementary School District #21 will submit a new 21st Century Community Learning Center (CCLC) application for the Cycle 15 Fiscal Year 2020 for W.R. Sullivan and Arthur M. Hamilton Schools. If approved the grant would be for a period of 5 years with a projected budget of $120,000 for Year 1, 2, & 3. The purpose of the grant is to (1) provide opportunities for academic enrichment, including providing tutorial services to help students, particularly students who attend low-performing schools, to meet the challenging State academic standards; (2) Offer youth development activities by providing enrichment opportunities (technology education, science, service learning, character education, etc. and to (3) offer families of students served by the program opportunities for active and meaningful engagement in their children's' education, including opportunities for literacy and related education development.
